{{Redirect|Independence Day}}
{{for|patriotic days not necessarily linked to independence|National day}}
[[File:National Days map.png|thumb|right|300px|{{legend|#008000|Independence-related National Day}} {{legend|#00FF00|Other [[National Day]]}} {{legend|#7F7F7F|No official National Day}}]]

An '''Independence Day''' is an annual event commemorating the [[anniversary]] of a [[nation]]'s independence or [[Sovereign state|statehood]], usually after ceasing to be a group or part of another nation or state; more rarely after the end of a [[military occupation]]; and in the unique case of Singapore, [[Singapore in Malaysia|expulsion from Malaysia]].

Most countries observe their respective independence days as [[National day|national holidays]].

