|Independence from the [[British Mandate for Palestine (legal instrument)|British Mandate for Palestine]], which took place on May&nbsp;14, 1948 (5&nbsp;Iyar 5708 in the [[Hebrew calendar]]). [[Yom Ha'atzmaut]] is celebrated on the Tuesday, Wednesday or Thursday nearest to 5&nbsp;Iyar, so it occurs between 3&nbsp;and 6&nbsp;Iyar each year; this means that the holiday can fall any time between and including April&nbsp;15 and May&nbsp;15, according to the [[Gregorian calendar]].
