{{notability|date=February 2017}}
'''Nude weather reports''' are weather reports performed in the nude, either on television or on radio, or in any other context.{{Citation needed|date=November 2009}}

==Examples==

'''Počasíčko''' (a diminutive of the [[Czech language|Czech]] word for weather) is the name of a late-night weather report that ran on [[Nova (Czech TV)|TV Nova]] in the [[Czech Republic]]. In this reverse [[strip tease]], a [[model (person)|model]] would appear in the nude and then gradually put on clothes appropriate for the next day's weather forecast. The programme aired for some time during 2002 and was then discontinued. It has resumed (in a reversed format, i.e., with "regular" strip-tease) on 1 February 2007.{{Citation needed|date=November 2009}}

'''Radio Tango''' in [[Norway]] was the world's first radio channel to broadcast nude weather reports, simultaneously providing a glimpse of the nude reporter on its web site.<ref name="radiotango">Reuters (2001-05-04). Radio Tango calls the tune in the nude. Reuters, 4 May 2001. Retrieved on 2006-04-02 from http://www.iol.co.za/index.php?set_id=1&click_id=29&art_id=qw988971542791B241.</ref>

